headline: Why Intel Stock Is Sinking Today
summary: A research note from Citi revealed that Intel's market share has fallen to its lowest level in more than two decades.  The troubled chipmaker is ceding market share to rival Arm Holdings.  Shares of Intel (NASDAQ: INTC) are falling on Wednesday.
